The earliest protocol of dubbo is the dubbo protocol, and rest is only supported in subsequent versions. 
You can understand that the reason why dubbo needs to implement the interface is the same as the reason why rest needs to know the path.

```
@DubboReference(
            check = false,
        methods = {
            @Method(name = "sayHelloAsync", onreturn = "service2_sayHelloAsync.onreturn")
        }
    )
 private Service2 service2;
```
这种方式可以启动。

